    "body": "@ekawibisono you are _actively_ configuring the node to be \"free for all\". \r\n\r\n` --allow-insecure-unlock  --unlock \"xxxx9E04\" --password password.txt --http.addr 0.0.0.0 --http.api admin,eth,miner,net,txpool,web3,debug,personal `. \r\n\r\nThose arguments can be translated into:\r\n\r\n> I want geth to be publically available to the internet (`--http.addr 0.0.0.0 --http.api admin,eth,miner,net,txpool,web3,debug,personal`) , and I want my account \".xxx9e04\" to be unlocked (`--unlock \"xxxx9E04\" --password password.txt`), so anyone can sign transactions from it without using a password. And yes, I am aware that this is insecure, but please go ahead anyway (`--allow-insecure-unlock`). \r\n\r\n",
